net.objectzoo.events.impl

Class Event4Distributor<T1,T2,T3,T4>

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.objectzoo.events.impl.Event4Distributor<T1,T2,T3,T4>
  • Type Parameters:
    T1 - The type of the first information parameter the event provides
    T2 - The type of the second information parameter the event provides
    T3 - The type of the third information parameter the event provides
    T4 - The type of the fourth information parameter the event provides
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Action4<T1,T2,T3,T4>, Event4<T1,T2,T3,T4>, Event4Delegate<T1,T2,T3,T4> 

    public class Event4Distributor<T1,T2,T3,T4>
extends Object
implements Event4Delegate<T1,T2,T3,T4>
    The Event4Distributor is a Event4Delegate implementation that allows event distribution to multiple subscribers. It is a helper class that encapsulates all the logic required to provide events in other classes. Subscriber invocations are performed in the order of subscription.
    Author:
    tilmann
